                {
                  "type": "section_title",
                  "title": "Comprehensive General Knowledge Guide",
                  "subtitle": "Connecting Mathematics, Biology, History, and Physics"
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "title": "Introduction to the Core Themes",
                  "body": "Our world is governed by a fascinating interplay of scientific principles and historical events. From the strict, undeniable laws of prime numbers and quadratic equations to the biological wonders of neuroplasticity and the historical impact of the Industrial Revolution, understanding these concepts requires a multifaceted approach."
                },
                {
                  "type": "key_definition",
                  "term": "Photosynthesis",
                  "body": "The metabolic process by which green plants and some other organisms use sunlight to synthesize nutrients from carbon dioxide and water. It is the foundation of most terrestrial life."
                },
                {
                  "type": "key_definition",
                  "term": "Neuroplasticity",
                  "body": "The brain's incredible ability to reorganize itself by forming new neural connections throughout life, fundamentally changing based on multifaceted, multidimensional stimuli."
                },
                {
                  "type": "warning",
                  "body": "Do not confuse the **Paris Agreement (2015)** on climate change mitigation with other historical treaties signed in the capital of France, such as the Treaty of Paris (1783)."
                },
                {
                  "type": "numbered_list",
                  "title": "Steps to solve any quadratic equation",
                  "items": [
                    {
                      "title": "Identify coefficients",
                      "description": "Determine the values of $a$, $b$, and $c$ in the standard form $ax^2 + bx + c = 0$."
                    },
                    {
                      "title": "Apply the formula",
                      "description": "Substitute the coefficients into the quadratic formula."
                    },
                    {
                      "title": "Calculate the roots",
                      "description": "Solve for the two possible values of $x$ using both the plus and minus variants."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "formula",
                  "title": "The Quadratic Formula",
                  "equation": "x = \\frac{-b \\pm \\sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}",
                  "equation_label": "Roots of a quadratic equation",
                  "body": "This formula allows you to find the roots of any polynomial equation of the second degree."
                },
                {
                  "type": "formula",
                  "title": "Area of a Circle",
                  "equation": "A = \\pi r^2",
                  "equation_label": "Where r is the radius of the circle"
                },
                {
                  "type": "quote",
                  "body": "I have not failed. I've just found 10,000 ways that won't work. True innovation is built upon cumulative knowledge.",
                  "author": "Thomas Edison (on the lightbulb)"
                },
                {
                  "type": "comparison_table",
                  "title": "Temperature Scales at Standard Atmospheric Pressure",
                  "columns": [
