    {
      "type": "single_choice",
      "text": "[Mixed] Calculate the area of a circle with radius $r = 5$. Use the formula $A = \\pi r^2$.",
      "options": [
        "The area is exactly $25\\pi$",
        "The area is approximately $78.54$",
        "If $r=5$, then $A = 10\\pi$ (Incorrect)",
        "None of the above options contains $\\pi$"
      ],
      "correct_answers": [
        0
      ],
      "explanation": "The area $A$ is given by $\\pi r^2$. With $r=5$, $A = \\pi (5^2) = 25\\pi$."
